TY  - JOUR
T1  - CEO Personality, Strategic Flexibility, and Firm Performance: The Case of the Indian Business Process Outsourcing Industry
AU  - Nadkarni, Sucheta
AU  - Herrmann, Pol
Y1  - 2010/10/01
PY  - 2010
DA  - 2010/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amj.2010.54533196
DO  - 10.5465/amj.2010.54533196
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 1050
EP  - 1073
VL  - 53
IS  - 5
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - We examine the relationships between CEO personality, strategic flexibility (ability to adapt quickly to environmental changes), and firm performance, using a sample of 195 small and medium-sized firms from the Indian business process outsourcing industry. We hypothesize that strategic flexibility mediates the relationships between CEO personality and firm performance. Our results extend previous research by not only highlighting the importance of CEO personality in driving strategic flexibility, but also indicating how each facet of CEO personality either enhances or inhibits strategic flexibility.
AB  - We examine the relationships between CEO personality, strategic flexibility (ability to adapt quickly to environmental changes), and firm performance, using a sample of 195 small and medium-sized firms from the Indian business process outsourcing industry. We hypothesize that strategic flexibility mediates the relationships between CEO personality and firm performance. Our results extend previous research by not only highlighting the importance of CEO personality in driving strategic flexibility, but also indicating how each facet of CEO personality either enhances or inhibits strategic flexibility.
